Pulmonary Reactive Uptake of Inhaled Toxic Contaminants PI: Edward M. Postlethwait, Ph.D.
University of Texas Medical Branch Pulmonary Division
The proposed project is designed to characterize and compare across species (including man) the kinetics of interaction and the predominant substrates involved during the pulmonary airspace absorption of NO, and 02 with the goal of establishing a model for evaluating relative dosimetry. The researchers will delineate the absorption determinants of NO, and 02 within the intact, isolated lung, followed by the determination of the extent to which uptake is localized to within the epithelial lining fluid (ELF).
